## Quick Storyboard — what to include on your 1–2 page Storyboard.pdf
- Title, date, author
- One-line summary (the headline insight)
- 3 supporting charts (each with 1-line caption + why it matters)
- 3 recommended actions (who, what, when)


---


## Short tips for chart choices (common scenarios)
- Time series (sales over time): line chart with moving average and annotated peaks.
- Comparison across categories: horizontal bar chart (sorted descending).
- Distribution of numeric variable: histogram or boxplot with outliers called out.
- Relationship between two variables: scatterplot + trend line; if many points, add density or hexbin.
- Part-to-whole (market share): consider bar or treemap; avoid 100% stacked bars unless necessary.


